name: floating hexagonal metal cage for aquaculture 6 m construction and maintenance | floating hexagonal metal cage | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/17942/documentation

This activity presents data from the Anchoveta Supply Chain project. Floating hexagonal metal cage for aquaculture, 6x6 m, used worldwide for salmonids, cichlids, etc. Used in lakes and river environments. This process may be used to model different sizes of floating hexagonal metal cages (observed range in lake Ttiticaca: 5x5 to 6.4x6.4).

Construction and maintenance of a floating cage system, expressed either in terms of its diameter (if floating collar) or side length (if hexagonal cage), with their associated lifetimes. The specific fish holding capacity of each system is expressed as well per m of diameter or side length.


EOL is included assuming a waste flow of 10% of all materials used in infrastructure.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/03:Fishing and aquaculture/032:Aquaculture

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Data from operations in the Titicaca lake (2012), Anchoveta Supply Chains project (http://anchoveta-sc.wikispaces.com). Lifetime: 5 years (structure) and 2 years (net)
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Floating cages used in the Titicaca lake and other Andean lakes were asumed to represent all types of floating cages used in lake-aquaculture producing countries in South America

exchanges.description: Floating hexagonal metal cage for lake and river aquaculture. Dimensions: 6x6 m, fish capacity: 1 000 kg
